Unison Co. jumped by the daily limit
in Seoul trading after  Toshiba Corp. (6502)  said it agreed to acquire
40 billion won of convertible bonds in the South Korean company
to enter the wind power business. Unison surged 15 percent to
5,310 won as of 9:15 a.m. on the Korea Exchange. The benchmark
Kospi Index fell 0.3 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
